cafes.name: Lone Star Pawz CATf√©
cafes.address: 8209 Broadway St #103, Pearland, TX 77581, USA

text.text:
I had a friend who visited this place before and liked the idea, I decided to try it as well.
At first glance, the place is super clean and tidy. The lounge is so comfortable and cozy :)

My kids enjoyed playing with the cats for an hour, they left before the hour as there wasn't that much to do with cats other than carrying them, I bet this place would have much more traffic if they added any cat-related activity to what they do already.
I enjoyed chatting with another visitor there which is one of the advantages of this cute sitting area.
Not too much options for snacks or drinks while waiting, i encourage them to have another thought about that option too like smoothies and healthy snacks to attract more people to it.

Overall, it is worth visiting and having fun with these cute cats over there.
The price is so reasonable as well.
Oh and the front desk girl was super nice and cooperative, I especially thank her for allowing me to bring our puppy with us and let him have his own fun time as well :)

üêæ‚ú® Just had the most purr-fect afternoon at the CATfe! For just $8, my son enjoyed a delightful experience that supports a great cause. He had a blast in the cozy cat cave, surrounded by the cutest cats, while I relaxed in the cafe sipping my coffee ‚òï.
The best part? No orders or hair to worry about‚Äîjust pure feline fun! If you're looking for a trendy spot to unwind and support our furry friends or looking to adopt, this is the place to be! Highly recommend! üê±‚ù§Ô∏è #CatCaf√© #GoodCause #FelineFun
This cat cafe was my first ever experience with cats and I absolutely loved it! The kitties are so adorable and sweet! I‚Äôll definitely be back again soon ü•∞

cafes.name: The Cozy Catfe
cafes.address: 740 SW Green Oaks Blvd #200, Arlington, TX 76017, USA

text.text: This was the first cat cafe that my wife and I have ever visited. We got two hours because we just lost our cat Sox of 20 years.  The owners were so welcoming and they offer a discount for veterans (free!).  We will definitely visit again soon.

This place was absolutely amazing, and the cats were all so adorable! I came here with some friends, and we all had a great time. The staff was extremely sweet and patient. I did get bitten by one of the shy kitties, but that was to be expected. Hope I was at least tasty. I would definitely recommend coming here!

What a great place with an awesome mission!

The Cozy Catfe has adorable kitties, a friendly staff, and great activities!

I went to Trivia Night and it was so much fun! In between rounds, we got to visit the cats in the cat room, which definitely beats what you'd get at a pub!

The cats are wonderful and the spaces they're in provide them with a lot of room and enrichment.

These cats are usually a little older, as the owner notes, because kittens are so quickly adopted. What the Cozy Catfe provides is nothing short of amazing -- it's a chance to socialize the cats AND for people to really get to know them one on one, rather than just choosing based on looks or behavior in a cage. Cats all have unique purr-sonalities, and Cozy Catfe gives them a chance to shine.

They're ready to meet people and to go to their forever homes. Is there anything more wonderful than that?

cafes.name: The Casual Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 7264 Glenview Dr, Richland Hills, TX 76180, USA

text.text:
I have got a membership on the first day.  So been here couple of times already. Plan to be there soon again atleast untill i can get a cat at my home.
The people here are amazing. Always so welcoming and smiley.
The cats are beyond adorable and well taken care of. Like as soon as you walk in u will know the people here really love those cuties. The cleanliness is another thing that sets them apart
We had a great time!  They have a few very young cats and a few were playing non-stop!  We are trying to heal after losing our cat Sox after 20 years with him.

The Casual Cat Cafe is such an amazing place! Giving these kitties a chance to get their forever homes. You can tell how much they love and care for the cats. My son was in the hospital for weeks and I was far away from my cats. I got to visit here a couple of times and it gave me such comfort to be with the cats and love on them. So even if you're not looking to adopt please go visit and support. The kitties love visitors. Also if you're interested in adopting there are some sweethearts that have been there awhile and they'd be such wonderful pets.  I recommend you find the quiet ones and give them some love too! There were several girls that weren't as outgoing as the others but they enjoyed being loved on.

cafes.name: 9 Whiskers Lounge
cafes.address: 510 S Mason Rd Suite H1, Katy, TX 77450, USA

text.text: This place is clean and so fun! This is a great time whether you‚Äôre here by yourself or your family. The staff is so sweet and knowledgeable. The cats are so sweet and energetic and I love that they bring out treats and encourage you to interact with the cats. Even better some of the cats are adoptable. We will definitely be back here!

This is such a wonderful place! The staff is super friendly and they told us all about the cats. The cats themselves are adorable and incredibly friendly. They loved to play with the provided toys and would walk right up for you to get pets and cuddles. We visited close to closing time, but we definitely plan on coming back earlier in the day to enjoy even more cat time. I can't wait to check out their events too!

I‚Äôve been to several cat cafes/lounges and this probably has to take the cake for one of the best experiences! Environment is super clean, calm, and relaxing. Owners/staff are super friendly and inviting. Most cats at other places seem stressed/distant to humans and don‚Äôt interact with you, but here, I had quite a few actually lie on my lap or play with my boyfriend and I! Would really recommend, I can tell the cats are well loved and taken care of here.

cafes.name: Cat Haven Lounge
cafes.address: 23015 Colonial Pkwy Suite B205, Katy, TX 77449, USA

text.text: Came here for the first time and I absolutely loved it! You can tell everyone here loves and cares for these cats. They have a good amount of adoptable  cats and good selection of merch. It‚Äôs very clean, has tons of toys, and cute photo op. The cats are very friendly and even more friendly if you purchase some treats to feed them. Fun and clean atmosphere and great staff!

It was pure delight to stumble upon Cat Haven Lounge today. My wife and I were looking to spend some time together. After not being able to go where we intended, we were surprised to find a cat lounge in Houston (katy).
The employees were welcoming and very patient. The lounge was really clean and smelled clean. Oh yeah, there were precious feline friends too. The cats were playful and loved hanging with guest. My wife and I had a blast and I hope to visit again soon.

Such an awesome experience! All the cats were so loving and friendly. The staff were also very kind and helpful. This was definitely the dopamine boost I needed after failing my exam lol. Definitely worth I‚Äôll come back.

cafes.name: Purrfecto Cat Lounge
cafes.address: 2300 S Lamar Blvd unit 104, Austin, TX 78704, USA

text.text: Oh. My. Goodness. The kittens were all so precious!! I like that they had some general rules to keep the cats safe, and everything seemed very well taken care of. Everything was also free-range and (obviously) hands-on. The drinks weren‚Äôt great, but that wasn‚Äôt what we were really there for anyway, so it just made for a nice sip-as-you-go sort of thing. All of the cats seemed to be pretty young, and I was surprised that all of them seemed to be happy to be loved on and held as well. They‚Äôre all rescues as well, and the adoption process seemed well set up and simple. The staff was great and attentive too. Super highly recommend!

This is the perfect spot to take someone who doesn‚Äôt own any cats üêà The kitties were so well behaved and, as you can see, super chill. I‚Äôd recommend going in the morning when there‚Äôs less people, but regardless you‚Äôll have a good time. Best part is, if you get attached to one of the cats you can adopt them (if they‚Äôre not already taken lol) :)

This place was so fun! I have been to one other cat cafe in Minneapolis and while that one has been around longer and is a bit more established, this one has its own features. I like the color coordinated atmosphere and most the cats are pretty young so they are more apt to play and cuddle.

I think the price is fair and it would be fun for all ages. I would like there to be more of the cafe aspect in the future- some coffee drinks, snacks, and cat toys or gifts for sale.

cafes.name: Fat Cats Organic Coffee & Desserts
cafes.address: 7020 Easy Wind Dr # 140, Austin, TX 78752, USA

text.text: I absolutely love visiting Fat Cats Bakery! As a vegan, it‚Äôs always a treat to be able to select any delicious item on the menu that I fancy! I recently enjoyed a ham and cheese croissant and chocolate donut; both were exceptional. I have had their empanadas in the past which are also amazing. Whether you are vegan or not, this place will knock your socks off plus it‚Äôs women-owned so that‚Äôs a bonus!

I‚Äôve been going here for years and the owner and baristas here are locals who are genuinely amazing people with a big heart and a huge passion for baked items. Try the croissants and empanadas, and their fruit kolaches on the weekends are out of this world!!!
Slow service but baked goods are SO amazing! I‚Äôm not even vegan, but I loved their croissants. Definitely give this place a shot. Also, the cat art and photos everywhere made my day.

cafes.name: Whiskers and Soda
cafes.address: 10320 Garland Rd, Dallas, TX 75218, USA

text.text:
Amazing gem of a place !

My wife and I brought our 3yr old and we had so much fun. We have two cats of our own and playing with the ones here was such an experience. The staff were really friendly and couldn't have made us feel more welcome, I really valued that.

All the cats are adoptable, they have all their shots and are fixed. This is a great way to find your forever companion as it lets you see who will connect with you. The coffee and pastries offered were delicious.
10/10 would recommend and will have to come back.

This place truly was worth the hour drive! I brought two of my friends and one of their little sisters (who is 9). The whole environment was outstanding! All of the employees were so kind and truly were the cherry on top of this already incredible experience! The cats are treated so well, and love people, they will run up to you and snuggle, play, or even just mess around with you, truly so fun! We had a blast and everyone already wants to go back, thank you Whiskers and Soda for providing a safe and fun environment for the kitties and thanks for sharing it with us! We‚Äôll be back soon!

Stumbled across the cutest cat cafe! They are also a cat hotel/ coffee shop where you can adopt the cats. There is a somewhat of a ‚Äúcover fee‚Äù to enter which covers the cats food and such. Very kind people working there who were super informative and friendly. The baristas were amazing and I loved my iced latte. The cutest cats and they also have a kitten room where you can play and pet the kittens!

cafes.name: El Gato Coffeehouse
cafes.address: 508 Pecore St, Houston, TX 77009, USA

text.text: Loved everything about this place! Very sweet, cute kitties. They had lots of space to run around and things to climb up. We really enjoyed our iced chai lattes and just hanging out with the kitties. They have a great mission and have rescued a lot of cats! I would highly recommend visiting if you are a cat lover.

This is an experience all about the cats! I love that they tell you before going in to respect the cats' wishes about being picked up, etc. Don't go here expecting to have something centered around food... or even the customers! This is about taking care of cats who need a home. There's an entry fee that helps take care of the cats. The cats have space, affection, good food, water, toys, etc, as they wait for forever homes, and I'm happy to get the opportunity to support that while also getting to spend time with the cats. That said, the cinnamon rolls are EXCELLENT! I also had iced tea, which was great. I'll keep coming back when I can and try the few other food items on the menu, along with the many drinks.

Loved this place.
Visited for a morning cat yoga class. Instructor was great and it was very relaxing. Having the cats all around you makes it a great and super cute experience. All cats are for adoption. They have some adults and some kittens, all well behaved so it's easy for you to pet all of them. Definitely reccomend!

cafes.name: Red Cat Jazz Cafe
cafes.address: 530 Texas Ave, Houston, TX 77002, USA

text.text: I had a wonderful experience during New Year's Eve. Everyone is so friendly and accommodating. Lots of good lighting options for ambiance. The owners had a soft opening during New Year's Eve to a packed house. I'm looking forward to y'all's Grand opening!

We had a great experience, Immerse yourself in the lively ambiance of Houston's Red Cat Jazz Cafe, where sensational music meets impeccable customer service. A must for jazz aficionados craving an unforgettable and enriching experience. We will be coming back.  ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ‚òÜ
Great place and great Jazz!

cafes.name: The Charming Cat Corner
cafes.address: 2401 S Stemmons Fwy, Lewisville, TX 75067, USA

text.text: One of the coolest cat cafes I've ever been to. They had several cats across multiple themed rooms. Plenty of toys to play. Kind workers who definitely care about each individual cat. I'd be a frequent visitor if I lived in the area!

I adopted Eeyore almost 2 years ago. He is the most gentle and loving animal I've ever had in my life. I should leave less stars because I'm going to be completely devistated when he leaves this world. This "cat" doesn't even bother Christmas trees... An alien. You gave me an alien... Alien cat-dog thing. Also thanks.

Literally the most adorable place, the workers are so sweet and gave us a walkthrough the place before anything. The separate themed rooms are adorable and so genius.
The feline leukemia room was really nice as well, it‚Äôs really nice that it‚Äôs a separate room, it gives you a bit of peace and quiet with the few kitties in there üòäLoved visiting!

cafes.name: C.A.T. Cafe Bakery - Coffee, Art, Tea
cafes.address: Inside the historic haunted Walker County Jail, 1012 University Ave, Huntsville, TX 77320, USA

text.text: Cute little place. I ordered a classic mocha and felt it was too sweet and that‚Äôs because it was sugar free or suppose to be. The baklava was pretty good. Small place to sit so be ready to take things to do
The drinks were great! Tried the coffee cake muffin and strawberry lemon poppyseed muffin. They were good and tasted fresh, but the coffee and lemon flavors are VERY subtle.

This was such a great place to stop and snack while exploring the Huntsville Square.
The Buffalo Chicken Dip was delicious, while not at all spicy, and the Dutch Chocolate Muffins were great. We enjoyed the Layered Lemonades and can't wait to try other drinks in the future.
We wandered around to enjoy the art and explore the small building while waiting on our food. The kids got a kick out of the booking wall, too.

cafes.name: Alley Cat Coffee
cafes.address: 2316 S Flores St, San Antonio, TX 78204, USA

text.text: Very easy to miss, but take the time to look them up....you will not regret it. Just happened to find it today and was wowed by a great caramel latte. I give Alley Cat props for a great latte primarily because you can taste the coffee first then the caramel. Not an overly sweet coffee drink. Very friendly and fast service. Support local and give them a try.

It took me a sec to realize Alley Cat was INSIDE Rios, but I'm so glad I found it. I got the cereal milk latte (cookie crisp), loved it, immediately started thinking of when I could come back. And Jasmine is so nice and friendly. I really enjoyed chatting while there.
Love the vibe, love the beans, love our barrista, Jasmine. 10/10 will always come back.

cafes.name: Tuxedo Cat‚Äôs Coffee
cafes.address: 6075 Heath Rd, San Antonio, TX 78250, USA

text.text: If you're looking for a peaceful escape, this charming coffee truck with an outdoor garden is the perfect spot. The serene atmosphere is complemented by the adorable cats that roam freely, adding an extra touch of warmth to your visit. Not only is it a beautiful place to unwind, but the coffee here is something truly special. Each cup boasts a unique, delicious flavor that‚Äôs unlike anything you‚Äôll find elsewhere. Whether you‚Äôre looking to relax, enjoy some great coffee, or just have a calm moment in nature, this is the place to be. Highly recommend it for anyone needing a peaceful retreat with a side of incredible coffee!

I got a strawberry mango smoothie which tasted better than I imagined. The location is one-of-a-kind. The drinks are a bit pricey but the beautiful location makes it feel a bit more worth it, especially if you stay/ walk around for a while. The cat that roams around there is so cute ü•∞

Had a very lovely time at Tuxedo Cat Cafe!! My parents and Bf loved their drinks. I got the lavender oat milk latte! I didn‚Äôt know about Mimi (Tuxedo Cat OG). May she RIP and continue guarding the cafe and walking around the gardens üôèü§çüñ§üêæüêà‚Äç‚¨õ. Never forgotten! I love my Tuxedo Cat bag and sticker that I purchased. Can‚Äôt wait to go again and walk around the gardens! Lizzie was very friendly and fun to talk to! :-)

cafes.name: Wildcat Cafe
cafes.address: 3606 N Ellison Dr, San Antonio, TX 78251, USA

text.text:
The Wild Cat Caf√© at Northwest Vista College is honestly one of my favorite spots on campus. Whether you need a quick bite or just want to chill between classes, this place has you covered since the library is next door. They‚Äôve got a good variety of drinks, snacks, and full meals, plus some great breakfast options if you‚Äôre up early. The hours are pretty convenient, they open at 7:00 a.m. to 7:00 p.m. Tuesday through Thursday, and on Fridays, they‚Äôre open from 8:00 a.m. to noon.

Inside, the caf√© can fit around 20 people, so it‚Äôs a nice spot to relax without feeling overcrowded. When the weather‚Äôs good, the outdoor seating is a perfect spot to hang out or study. I also love that most students pay with their school ID, which makes it super easy and convenient.

If you‚Äôre ever wondering what to order, I personally recommend their sandwiches and wraps. They‚Äôre always fresh, filling, and perfect for when you need something quick and delicious. It‚Äôs just a really chill, welcoming place that makes it easy to take a break from the busyness of college life. Whether you‚Äôre grabbing breakfast, lunch, or just a snack, The Wild Cat Caf√© is definitely worth checking out.
Would give zero stars if I could

cafes.name: Fat Cat Lounge and Cafe
cafes.address: 301 Main St, Smithville, TX 78957, USA

text.text: Absolutely LOVED this place! We stumbled upon fat cat lounge after our original idea for a birthday dinner was packed with a birthday party, and I am so glad we did! The atmosphere is so relaxed and welcoming, like going to a friends house, and the (I think) owner and the waitress were amazing and helpful with wine and food selection! But the crown jewel of this place, the food; I don‚Äôt even know how to describe how wonderful the food was but it was wonderful to say the least. We collectively had the creamy Jalapeno dip, lasagna, a bison burger, and bread pudding! Everything is homemade, including the dressing (blue cheese was fantastic) I recommend all of it! Just go there, you will love it!
Delicious Chicken Alfredo + Sandwich! The bread and bacon were crunchy to perfection and the sauce delicious! Service was also very friendly :) would 100% recommend
One of the best burgers I‚Äôve had! They have farm to table beef, which is hard to find now days. The atmosphere is great as well. I plan on coming back ASAP!

cafes.name: Alley Cats Coffee Bar
cafes.address: 305 E Front St, Texarkana, AR 71854, USA

text.text: Outstanding! This is what comes to mind when I think of Alley Cats. The folks there today were awesome, very kind hearted and friendly. The owner talked with us for a while and got one of their alley cats to come out to us. You could see his heart in all he said. Truly one of the best places. The coffees are unique and their savory breakfast waffles with hot honey, just wonderful! Thank you guys for sharing you little bit of paradise with our family! We enjoyed every second.

This place is simply awesome! The staff are super friendly and the coffee is great‚Ä¶ Oh and don‚Äôt forget about the avocado (or banana) toast. If you‚Äôre passing by this place is worth the stop. The decor and coffee shop alone are worth a pit stop and the coffee doesn‚Äôt disappoint. If you want to get experimental, try the spicy Myan mocha (with chocolate or cinnamon). Enjoy!

This place is so fun! One of the most unique coffee shops I've ever been to. Also woman-owned and a big supporter of local artists! The barista was super friendly. The tea and coffee are so good! I'm from Houston but I really hope I can come back! (Also yes it's an actual retired train car but it does have AC and working bathrooms!)

cafes.name: Sun City Kitty
cafes.address: 750 Sunland Park Dr H09, El Paso, TX 79912, USA

text.text: My son  really liked one of the cats he bonded with it and wanted to adopt it. The cat had on the board,  it was more shy more reserved , not  very outgoing, which was perfect for us. We  were not able to adopt this cat due to the employee saying that the cat didn't want to bond with my son. I don't believe that was true, the environment was not suitable. They had kids in there screaming, all the cats were trying to run away because of the loud noise. I truly believe because I did not give a tip when I paid for our visit they were being retaliatory against us. My son is autistic with special needs. This cat would've been perfect for him. He was visibly crying, I will definitely be telling my military community not to come here. The service is horrible.

My two teenage nieces and I thought this was a great way to spend an hour!  Lots of cuddly kitties all eager to play.  It sure seemed like the cats enjoyed us as much as we enjoyed them.  The hour package was the right amount of time (for only $3 more than the 30 minute package).  Cats really loved the treats, but since they only let you buy one per person, make sure you don't give them out in the first few minutes.  The coffee was excellent.  Can't wait to go back.

Well this place is alright I would lowkey say it‚Äôs a waste of money, the bag where the cat treats were are soooo small they only had 6 tiny little treats . The cats are literally spoiled because they will not interact with you unless you give them treats. And most cats there are aggressive which is normal cat behavior but still kinda shitty. The drinks are not that good too , either too much sugar or not enough. The place is also dirty it was full of cat shit and the cats smelled dirty and dusty . If you think you will get your own time with the cats then you are WRONG . When I went I thought it would only be me and my bf but more people came in and took most of the cats leaving us with almost none. They are cute but that was definitely not what I was expecting for my first visit. If you are visiting be prepared to get bored lol.

cafes.name: Kitty's Cafe
cafes.address: 18904 FM 1488, Magnolia, TX 77355, USA

text.text: Fantastic breakfast! Had 2 eggs, hash browns, biscuit, and sausage (took home leftovers)‚Ä¶ shared a ¬Ω biscuit with sausage gravy with a friend‚Ä¶ the BEST biscuits and sausage gravy I‚Äôve ever had‚Ä¶ chatted a bit with Ms. Kitty herself, she and her staff are kind and helpful‚Ä¶ will definitely be back!

Horrible experience, was told it would be 20 minutes for a to go order which turned out to be an hour long wait, food was lukewarm, multiple items in the order were wrong, have been going here for year but will not be going back after this, go to magnolia diner instead. Also we got some cobbler which was completely raw!

Ah, such a gem! This is where the locals go! Open for breakfast and lunch. I had the eggs and hash browns and it was delicious. Went a few minutes before closing time but was met with a smile and patience to finish my food. I would recommend you come and experience to local breakfast spot where everyone knows everyone!

cafes.name: CatCafe Lounge | Cats + Kittens + Catio
cafes.address: 1736 S Sepulveda Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 90025, USA

text.text: This place is very small, but it is very clean, well maintained, and comforting not only for the guests, but most importantly, for the cats. The reservation fee is pricey, however this business is a non profit that focuses on rehabilitating rescued cats, and it has a great mission and appears to be working very hard and ethically to give these cats a chance at adoption. The cats have plenty of space to roam around and sit, sleep, and play anywhere they like. The cats also have easy access to food, water, and litter boxes. I highly recommend this location for anyone who loves cats. You‚Äôll have a great time here and the time will fly by too fast. It is also a great business to support! I‚Äôll definitely be coming back soon ;)

My son loves this place and all the kitties! Our cat is mature and doesn‚Äôt play with him, so he was absolutely thrilled when little kittens started playing with him and following him. I really like that they have a nice outdoor catio where cats enjoy sunshine and chill.
Friendly staff and such a huge amount of space for the kitties. Cats looked very well taken care of and space was clean as well. I loved the mixed outdoor/indoor space.
